00:12:47.360 --> 00:12:49.256
AG: Ronan, when you talk about systems,

00:12:49.280 --> 00:12:51.096
it's tempting to look at this problem

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:53.856
and say what we need
are systems that essentially identify

00:12:53.880 --> 00:12:55.656
and root out bad apples.

00:12:55.680 --> 00:12:58.616
But there's also a little bit
of a bad barrel story here,

00:12:58.640 --> 00:13:01.016
where some of this behavior
gets normalized